1.23:
Turn at my reproof;
    surely I will pour out my spirit on you;
    I will make my words known to you.

3.3:
Do not let mercy and truth forsake you;
    bind them around your neck,
    write them on the tablet of your heart,

4.4:
He also taught me and said to me,
    “Let your heart retain my words;
    keep my commandments, and live.

5.19:
Let her be as the loving deer and pleasant doe;
    let her breasts satisfy you at all times;
    and always be enraptured with her love.

6.3:
Do this now, my son, and deliver yourself;
    when you have come into the hand of your friend,
go and humble yourself;
    plead with your friend.

6.13:
He winks with his eyes,
    he signals with his feet,
    he motions with his fingers;

6.22:
When you go, they will lead you;
    when you sleep, they will keep you;
    and when you awake, they will speak with you.

8.13:
The fear of the Lord is to hate evil;
    pride and arrogance
    and the evil way and the perverse mouth I hate.

8.30:
then I was by Him, as one brought up with Him;
and I was daily His delight,
    rejoicing always before Him,

22.29:
Do you see a man diligent in his business?
    He will stand before kings;
    he will not stand before obscure men.

23.5:
Will you set your eyes on that which is not?
    For riches certainly make themselves wings;
    they fly away as an eagle toward heaven.

23.31:
Do not look on the wine when it is red,
    when it sparkles in the cup,
    when it swirls around smoothly;

24.14:
so shall the knowledge of wisdom be to your soul;
    when you have found it, then there will be a reward,
    and your expectation will not be cut off.

24.27:
Prepare your work outside,
    and make it fit for yourself in the field;
    and afterwards build your house.

25.8:
Do not go forth hastily to strive;
    lest you do not know what to do in the end,
    when your neighbor has put you to shame.

27.10:
Do not forsake your own friend or your father’s friend,
    nor go into your brother’s house in the day of your calamity;
    for better is a neighbor who is near than a brother far off.

27.27:
You will have goats’ milk enough
    for your food, for the food of your household,
    and for the maintenance of your maidens.

28.10:
Whoever causes the righteous to go astray in an evil way,
    he himself will fall into his own pit;
    but the upright will have good things in possession.

28.17:
A man burdened with bloodshed of any person
    will flee until death;
    let no man help him.

30.8:
Remove vanity and lies far from me—
    give me neither poverty nor riches;
    feed me with food convenient for me;

30.20:
Such is the way of an adulterous woman;
    she eats and wipes her mouth,
    and says, “I have done no wickedness.”

31.4:
It is not for kings, O Lemuel,
    it is not for kings to drink wine,
    nor for princes strong drink;
